  user_id UUID REFERENCES users(id),
  workout_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  duration INTERVAL
);

CREATE TABLE fitness_logs (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id UUID REFERENCES users(id),
  workout_id UUID REFERENCES workouts(id),
  exercise_id UUID REFERENCES exercises(id),
  date DATE NOT NULL,
  sets INT,
  reps INT
);

CREATE TABLE exercises (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  exercise_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  muscle_group VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE users (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  age INT
);</t><s>insert into users (id, username, email, age) values ('9e1202c6-3e7e-464b-a2d5-730adb3dc4c1', 'john_doe', 'john.doe@example.com', 30);</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);</t><s>INSERT INTO users (user_id, username, email, age, gender, created_at) VALUES ('1a2b3c4d-5e6f-7g8h-9i0j', 'john_doe', 'john.doe@example.com', 30, 'Male', '2022-01-01 00:00:00');</s>

);

);

    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);</t><s>INSERT INTO activities (activity_name, description, difficulty_level, created_at) VALUES ('Running', 'Run for 30 minutes', 5, '2022-01-01 08:00:00');</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);</t><s>INSERT INTO activities (activity_name, description, difficulty_level, created_at) VALUES ('Running', 'Run for 30 minutes', 5, '2022-01-01 08:00:00');</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);</t><s>INSERT INTO activities (activity_name, description, difficulty_level, created_at) VALUES ('Running', 'Run for 30 minutes', 5, '2022-01-01 08:00:00');</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE activities (
    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);</t><s>insert into workouts (user_id, activity_id, start_time, end_time, duration, calories_burned) values ('1a2b3c4d-5e6f-7g8h-9i0j', 1, '2022-01-01 08:00:00', '2022-01-01 08:30:00', '30 minutes', 200);</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE progress (
    progress_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    goal_id INT NOT NULL,
    progress INT,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (goal_id) REFERENCES goals(goal_id)
);

    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE goals (
    goal_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    goal_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target INT,
    deadline DATE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
    workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID NOT NULL,
    activity_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    end_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    duration INTERVAL,
    calories_burned INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (activity_id) REFERENCES activities(activity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

    activity_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,

    description TEXT,
    difficulty_level INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
